A teenager was pinned under a bus and critically injured Friday evening near the Tidal Basin, authorities said. The incident occurred around 7 p.m. on West Basin Drive near the memorial to the Rev. Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. After being extricated from under the bus the teenager was flown to a hospital by U.S. Park Police helicopter. His condition was said to be extremely critical. It appeared that the bus was a commercial vehicle, but it was not immediately clear who operated it. The circumstances of the incident remained unclear Friday night.